[[File:MLP Equestria Girls - Rainbow Rocks Comic-Con EXCLUSIVE Teaser|thumb|right|300px|Official ''Rainbow Rocks'' trailer, first shown at Comic-Con.]]
On February 13, 2014, Entertainment Weekly published an article about the film. Details about its plot were limited; however, the article included a trailer showcasing several clips and a [[Shake your Tail!|new song]] by 丹尼尔·英格拉姆, all from the [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks/Animated shorts|animated shorts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ishiH3Art/status/451527737627254784|title=ishiH3Art: @JamieKilpatrick because all ...|author=Ishi Rudell|publisher=Twitter|date=2014-04-03|accessdate=2014-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ishiH3Art/status/456905505928380416|title=ishiH3Art: “@ErcJac: @ishiH3Art Will ...|author=Ishi Rudell|publisher=Twitter|date=2014-04-17|accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ishiH3Art/status/458264755434577920|title=ishiH3Art: “@nhSnork: at this point, ...|author=Ishi Rudell|publisher=Twitter|date=2014-04-21|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://family-room.ew.com/2014/02/13/my-little-pony-equestria-girls-rainbow-rocks/|title='My Little Pony Equestria Girls': Yes, there will be a sequel. And we've got a clip! EXCLUSIVE|author=Hillary Busis|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=2014-02-13|accessdate=2014-02-13}}</ref>

As part of the [[Wikipedia:San Diego Comic-Con International|San Diego Comic-Con International]] "Hasbro Studios: My Little Pony Friendship Is Magic and My Little Pony Equestria Girls" panel on July 25, 2014, "Guests from Hasbro Studios ''My Little Pony Friendship Is Magic'' airing on the Hub Network in the U.S. and ''My Little Pony Equestria Girls'' share details of the making of the popular animated series and a sneak peek into the new ''My Little Pony Equestria Girls Rainbow Rock''{{sic}} movie coming this fall."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comiccon2014.sched.org/event/d93e17202fadc4c8c969ae82801a840f|title=Comic-Con 2014: Hasbro Studios: My Little Pony Friendshi...|publisher=Sched|accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref>

On July 24, 2014, Yahoo! TV posted not only a new trailer for the film, but also a [[Battle|song]] performed by [[the Dazzlings]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/blogs/tv-news/first-look---my-little-pony--posse-goes-up-against-a--mean--girl-group-in--equestria-girls-%E2%80%94-rainbow-rocks--003226065.html|title=First Look: 'My Little Pony' Posse Goes Up Against a (Mean) Girl Group In 'Equestria Girls — Rainbow Rocks'|author=Yahoo TV|work=Yahoo TV|date=2014-07-24|accessdate=2014-07-24}}</ref>In the teaser, Rainbow Dash was removed from the shot where Sunset says, "I turned into a raging she-demon."

On September 10, 2014, Shout! Factory, through Equestria Daily, revealed a new 30-second trailer including more footage of both pony and human Twilight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E5r0qa4aOBU|title=EQD Exclusive: Equestria Girls Rainbow Rocks 30 Second Shout Factory Promo|work=YouTube|date=2014-09-10|accessdate=2014-09-10}}</ref>Two days later on September 12, a 50-second trailer was released on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gjJ4gLcdnIM|title=Equestria Girls Trailer Highlights More Characters!|publisher=YouTube|date=2014-09-12|accessdate=2014-09-12}}</ref>Six days later on September 18, a full theatrical trailer was released on Yahoo! TV;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/video/little-pony-trailer-193654227.html|title='My Little Pony: Equestria Girls — Rainbow Rocks' Trailer|publisher=[[Wikipedia:Yahoo!|Yahoo! TV]]|date=2014-09-18|accessdate=2014-09-18}}</ref>the trailer was uploaded to Hasbro's YouTube channel four days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M-N2Fn1tP3Q|title=MLP: Equestria Girls Rainbow Rocks - Official Movie Trailer #1|publisher=YouTube|date=2014-09-22|accessdate=2014-09-22}}</ref>

