===Live-action music videos===
On February 20, 2014, Hasbro released a live-action music video on their official website depicting six young females as [[the Rainbooms]] in a rock band. Like the similar ''Magic of Friendship'' music video released to tie-in with the first movie, the ''Rainbow Rocks'' music video uses a rock version of [[Equestria Girls (Cafeteria Song)]] and shows the Mane Six's human counterparts in animated form doing the "EG Stomp".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ikAh9bjKmi4|title=Equestria Girls™ Rainbow Rocks Part 1|work=YouTube|date=2014-02-27|accessdate=2014-03-27}}</ref>

On August 4, 2014, Hasbro released a second live-action music video depicting the Rainbooms as well as the Dazzlings and [[DJ Pon-3]] in a rock competition. The rock version of [[Equestria Girls (Cafeteria Song)|Equestria Girls]] from the previous video plays with lyrics from [[Under Our Spell]], [[Shine Like Rainbows]], and the [[Rainbow Rocks (song)|''Rainbow Rocks'' title song]] included.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pS5xwYsDjZ8|title=MLP Equestria Girls™ Rainbow Rocks Part 2|work=YouTube|date=2014-08-04|accessdate=2014-08-05}}</ref>

==Release==
===Theatrical===
Like ''Equestria Girls'' before it, this film was distributed to American and Canadian theaters in limited release on September 27, 2014. It also received a 'Purple Carpet' premiere at the [[wikipedia:TCL Chinese Theatre|Chinese Theatre]] in Hollywood, which was attended by the cast and crew as well as some celebrities such as [[wikipedia:Jamie Foxx|Jamie Foxx]], ''[[wikipedia:Modern Family|Modern Family]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s [[wikipedia:Ariel Winter|Ariel Winter]], and Academy Award nominee [[wikipedia:Quvenzhané Wallis|Quvenzhané Wallis]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.shoutfactory.com/editorials/rainbow-rocks-premiere | title = Rainbow Rocks Premiere | publisher = [[Wikipedia:Shout! Factory|Shout Factory]] | date = 2014-10-06 | accessdate = 2014-10-09 }}</ref>

''Rainbow Rocks'' was released on October 25 and 26, 2014 in the [[Wikipedia:United Kingdom|United Kingdom]].<ref name="Myvue" />The film was released on November 15, 2014 in [[Wikipedia:Australia|Australia]].<ref name="Event" />

===Home media===
''My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks'' was released on DVD and Blu-ray on October 28, 2014, a little over a month after the theatrical release. Special features include a new featurette, the first eight [[Rainbow Rocks animated shorts|animated shorts]] that were released on YouTube, three sing-along songs, and audio commentary by screenwriter 梅根·麦卡锡, director [[Jayson Thiessen]], co-director [[Ishi Rudell]], VP of Development at Hasbro Mike Vogel, and executive director of Hasbro Brian Lenard.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.phase4films.com/Details.aspx?projectId=ca48cd13-b0cc-e311-a08d-d4ae527c3b65|title=My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks DVD Factsheet|work=Phase 4 Films|date=2014-07-01|accessdate=2014-08-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.equestriadaily.com/2014/10/rainbow-rocks-blu-ray-audio-commentary.html|title=Rainbow Rocks Blu-Ray Audio Commentary Cast Revealed|author=Sethisto|work=Equestria Daily|date=2014-10-01|accessdate=2014-10-02}}</ref>There are also three store exclusives for the DVD only. The [[Wikipedia:Target Corporation|Target]] edition includes a bracelet, a $4 coupon for one MLP toy, and the original ''Equestria Girls'' DVD. The [[Wikipedia:Walmart|Walmart]] edition includes [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls - Rainbow Rocks CD|a music CD]], a digital copy of the film, and the same $4 coupon. The [[Wikipedia:Kmart|Kmart]] edition includes a "backstage pass" and the coupon.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.therockfather.com/news-and-reviews/movie-and-tv/item/2900-my-little-pony-equestria-girls-rainbow-rocks-heads-home-on-blu-ray-and-dvd|title=My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks heads home on Blu-ray and DVD...|author=James Zahn|work=The Rock Father|date=2014-10-13|accessdate=2014-10-13}}</ref>Upon initial release, the DVD version of the film had an error in which chapters 5 and 6 play in reverse when the DVD is played from the main menu ‘Play’ listing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://shoutfactory.com/film/film-animation/my-little-pony-equestria-girls-rainbow-rocks|title=My Little Pony: Equestria Girls - Rainbow Rocks|publisher=Shout! Factory|date=2014-10-28|accessdate=2014-10-28}}</ref>Shout! Factory has a listing on their site where a free replacement disc can be sent.

A Region 2 ''Rainbow Rocks'' DVD by Primal Screen Entertainment was released on March 23, 2015 for various countries, including [[Wikipedia:France|France]], [[Wikipedia:Italy|Italy]], [[Wikipedia:Netherlands|Netherlands]], [[Wikipedia:Spain|Spain]], and the [[Wikipedia:United Kingdom|United Kingdom]].<ref name="AmazonUK" />

Alongside ''Equestria Girls'' and ''Friendship Games'', this film was released in a box set on October 13, 2015 in Region 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.com/My-Little-Pony-Equestria-Lenticular/dp/B0112HPRLG/|title=My Little Pony: Equestria Girls (Three Movie Gift Set)|publisher=[[Wikipedia:Amazon.com|Amazon.com]]|date=2015-07-23|accessdate=2015-07-23}}</ref>

===Television===
{{for|list of changes to Discovery Family's initial television broadcast of Rainbow Rocks|/Television edits}}
The film made its TV debut on the newly rebranded Discovery Family on October 17, 2014. On November 8, 2014, it made its premiere on [[Wikipedia:Family Channel|Family Channel]] in Canada. On November 15, 2014, it made its premiere on [[Wikipedia:Disney Channel (Spain)|Disney Channel]] in Spain. An Italian dub of the film premiered on the [[Wikipedia:Boomerang (Italy)|Boomerang]] channel in Italy on November 16, 2014.<ref name="Blogo" />In the UK, the film premiered on [http://www.popfun.co.uk Pop] on December 24, 2014 with no cuts.

